        <h3>Enhancement by adding more articles on the study of religion</h3>
        <h4>Project "Articles in Collective works"</h4>
        <p>With the beginning of the second project phase 2019-2021, the ‘FID Study of Religion’ has started to identify the numerous articles that are hidden in collections of essays (i.e.: anthologies, festschrifts, congress volumes, etc.) and is going to index them in Relbib. The better retrieval of such contributions is an urgent desideratum by the study of religion community.</p>

        <h4>Project "Retro Cataloguing"</h4>
        <p>Another request from study of religion scholars was to index older articles from relevant journals. Some 40 journals will be retro-catalogued with the help of semi-automatic metadata acquisition and, as far as possible, subject indexed.</p>

        <h3>Strengthening Open Access activities</h3>
        <h4>Self archiving service</h4>
        <p>The ‘FID Study of Religion’ supports the publication and accessibility of literature in its discipline by operating a specialist repository for <a href="<?=$this->url('content-page', ['page' => 'self_archiving_service'])?>">self archiving publications</a>.</p>

        <h5>Open Journal Platform</h5>
        <p>We help publishers of journals and series who wish to offer their journal open access on how to set up or switch to the <a href="<?=$this->url('content-page', ['page' => 'ojs'])?>">OJS platform.</a></p>

        <h4>Information on research data management</h4>
        <p>The discourse on the handling of <a href="<?=$this->url('content-page', ['page' => 'research_data_management'])?>">research data</a> plays an important role in an increasingly digital research world. The FID supports scholars of the study of religion for any questions they may have on the subject.</p>


        <h3>Collaborations</h3>
        <p>With the help of cooperations, the ‘FID Study of Religion’ seeks to improve its services. In the context of a continuous expansion of the RelBib database, cooperation with editorial teams of journals is sought for, as well as cooperations with institutions.</p>

        <h3><a href="<?=$this->url('content-page', ['page' => 'cooperative_cataloguing'])?>">Cooperative cataloguing</a> with editorial teams</h3>
        <p>Editorial teams or interested academics can use a script of the Open Access Software Zotero to index their journal's articles themselves and submit them to RelBib.</p>

        <h3>Project: Indexing of the REMID archive</h3>
        <p>With the start of the second funding phase (2018-2021), the Institute for Comparative Studies in Culture and Religion at the University of Marburg, REMID e.V. and the University Library of Marburg could be won as <a href="<?=$this->url('content-page', ['page' => 'cooperations_institutions'])?>">cooperation partners</a>. The aim of the Marburg subproject is to make the REMID e.V. archive accessible.</p>

        <h3>Cooperation with other FIDs</h3>
        <p>On an informal level we cooperate with the <a target="_blank" href="//crossasia.org">FID CrossAsia</a> and the <a target="_blank" href="//bibliothek.uni-halle.de/projekte/fid_nahost/">FID Middle East, North Africa and Islamic Studies</a>.</p>
